                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" id="ageofenlightenment_sng_1" hclass="sense"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a period in Europe in the 18th century when many writers and <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/thinker#thinker_topg_1" title="thinkers definition"><span class="ndv">thinkers</span></a> began to question established beliefs, e.g. in the authority of kings or of the Church, in favour of reason and scientific proof. The idea developed that everyone was of equal value and had equal rights.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
